<p>If my project uses <code>Promise</code> a lot, is it a good idea to resolve promises for all arguments when writing a function? For example,</p>  <pre><code>function foo (arg1, arg2, arg3) {     // do stuff with arg1, arg2, arg3 }  let pArg1 = getArg1Async(); let pArg2 = pArg1.then(calcArg2Async); let pArg3 = getArg3Async();  let p = Promise.join(pArg1, pArg2, pArg3, foo); </code></pre>  <p>becomes</p>  <pre><code>function foo(pArg1, pArg2, pArg3) {     return Promise.join(pArg1, pArg2, pArg3, function(arg1, arg2, arg3) {         // do stuff with arg1, arg2, arg3     }); }  let pArg1 = getArg1Async(); let pArg2 = pArg1.then(calcArg2Async); let pArg3 = getArg3Async();  let p = foo(pArg1, pArg2, pArg3); </code></pre>